{# SeverActions override of SkyrimNet's 0020_format_rules.                          #}
{# Single source of truth for length / sentence counts in dialogue.                 #}
{#                                                                                  #}
{# Why override: previously SkyrimNet's 0020 + our 0260 + our 0400 all set          #}
{# different caps that stacked in the LLM's head. This file owns length; all       #}
{# other SeverActions prompts must NOT declare sentence counts or word caps.       #}
{{ render_subcomponent("guidelines", render_mode) }}

## Length
{% if render_mode == "thoughts" or render_mode == "book" %}
{% if is_in_combat(npc.UUID) %}
Combat: 8-30 words. First sentence 10 words or fewer. Raw, visceral, immediate.
{% elif render_mode == "book" %}
8-90 words depending on relevance. Brief for mundane books, expand for meaningful content.
{% else %}
8-30 words. First sentence 10 words or fewer.
{% endif %}
{% elif render_mode == "transform" %}
8-45 words. Keep it natural to how you speak.
{% else %}
{% if decnpc(npc.UUID).isInCombat %}
Combat: 1 sentence, maximum 14 words. Urgent and brief.
{% else %}
1-3 sentences (8-40 words typical). Do NOT write multiple paragraphs. 60 words maximum.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{% if render_mode == "thoughts" or render_mode == "book" %}
## Grounding
Base thoughts only on: your character profile, listed memories, scene description, and recent events.
Do not: invent new facts, assume specific outcomes, retell past events, or drift into unrelated worries.
{% endif %}
